               <note type="abstract">H.P. Collins sends to J.G.M. Ramsey an original poem written about their friendship and their advancing age.  It mentions sad events they have encountered, patience they would need to overcome bad things, mercy they&apos;d been given to get through afflictions, the bad along with the good. He writes about his wish that Ramsey will always be happy and content even if they should not meet again.




  



